      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Bonhams estimates that the Meyers Manx will sell for between $400,000 and $600,000, which isn't a bad price premium when you consider that McQueen not only drove the buggy but he also had a hand in building and designing it. On top of its famous driver and star car status, this Meyers Manx is completely customized with a unique body with an eye-catching orange paint job with lots of chrome and American Racing wheels. The interior is equally custom with quilted stitching a two-seater seating arrangement. Instead of the Meyers Manx's factory VW engine, this buggy is powered by a ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Chevrolet Corvair",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.bonhams.com/auctions/25719/lot/119/?utm_source=motorious.com&utm_medium=article&utm_campaign=motorious",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " that was enhanced by Off-Road Motorsports Hall of Fame inductee, Pete Condos.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "According to Bonhams, McQueen once said this about his dune buggy:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "“I helped them design it, so I’m kinda proud of that. It’s set on a Volkswagen chassis with big ol’ wide weenies – big wide tires on mag wheels, Corvair engine stuffed in the back…It’s very light, you know. It’s pulling about 230 horses and weighs about a thousand pounds.”",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "quote",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In addition to the above McQueen's dune buggy action is nowhere near as action-packed (or time consuming) as his famous ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
